[32m+[m[32m# 🤖 Enterprise GenAI Knowledge Assistant[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m> A production-grade **Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)** system that lets organizations query internal documents using natural language — with zero hallucination and enterprise-level security.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 📌 Overview[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe Enterprise GenAI Knowledge Assistant transforms unstructured enterprise documents into a conversational AI interface. Built on RAG architecture, it ensures every response is **grounded in your actual documents** — not model hallucinations.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## ❗ Problem Statement[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mOrganizations struggle with knowledge retrieval because:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Information is scattered across hundreds of documents[m
[32m+[m[32m- Traditional keyword search lacks semantic understanding[m
[32m+[m[32m- Public AI tools risk data leakage[m
[32m+[m[32m- General-purpose LLMs hallucinate facts not present in source material[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 💡 Solution[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis system implements a full RAG pipeline:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Ingests enterprise documents (PDF, DOCX, HTML, TXT)[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Extracts and chunks text intelligently[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Generates semantic embeddings[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Stores and indexes them in a vector database[m
[32m+[m[32m5. On query — retrieves the most relevant chunks[m
[32m+[m[32m6. Feeds context to an LLM to generate a grounded answer[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mResponses are **strictly derived from your uploaded documents**.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 🏗️ Architecture[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mDocument Upload → Text Extraction → Chunking → Embedding Generation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                        ↓[m
[32m+[m[32m                                              Vector Database (FAISS / ChromaDB)[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                        ↓[m
[32m+[m[32mUser Query → Semantic Retrieval (Top-K) → LLM (Mistral / Phi3:mini) → Grounded Answer[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 🧠 Key Features[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- ✅ Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)[m
[32m+[m[32m- ✅ Semantic search using dense embeddings[m
[32m+[m[32m- ✅ Context-aware, source-grounded answers[m
[32m+[m[32m- ✅ Hallucination control[m
[32m+[m[32m- ✅ Chat-based UI[m
[32m+[m[32m- ✅ Scalable and modular architecture[m
[32m+[m[32m- ✅ Enterprise data stays local / private[m
[32m+[m[32m- ✅ Runs fully offline using Ollama[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 🛠️ Tech Stack[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Layer | Technology |[m
[32m+[m[32m|---|---|[m
[32m+[m[32m| Frontend | React.js, Tailwind CSS |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Backend | Python, FastAPI |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Embeddings | BGE |[m
[32m+[m[32m| LLMs | Mistral, Phi3:mini (via Ollama) |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Vector DB | FAISS, ChromaDB |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 📂 Supported Document Types[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- PDF (`.pdf`)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Word Documents (`.docx`)[m
[32m+[m[32m- HTML (`.html`)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Plain Text (`.txt`)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## ⚙️ Getting Started[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Prerequisites[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Python 3.9+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Node.js 18+[m
[32m+[m[32m- [Ollama](https://ollama.com) — for running LLMs locally[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Step 1: Install Ollama & Pull Models[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDownload and install Ollama from [https://ollama.com/download](https://ollama.com/download), then pull the required models:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mollama pull mistral[m
[32m+[m[32mollama pull phi3:mini[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m> ⚠️ **Important:** You must start the Ollama server before running the project.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mollama serve[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mKeep this running in a terminal throughout your session.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Step 2: Clone the Repository[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mgit clone <repo url>[m
[32m+[m[32mcd Enterprise-GenAI-Knowledge-Assistant[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Step 3: Backend Setup[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mcd backend[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Create and activate a virtual environment[m
[32m+[m[32mpython -m venv venv[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# On Windows[m
[32m+[m[32mvenv\Scripts\activate[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# On macOS/Linux[m
[32m+[m[32msource venv/bin/activate[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Install dependencies[m
[32m+[m[32mpip install -r requirements.txt[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Step 4: Frontend Setup[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mcd frontend[m
[32m+[m[32mnpm install[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## ▶️ Running the Application[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mMake sure `ollama serve` is running first, then:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32m# Terminal 1 — Start the backend[m
[32m+[m[32mcd backend[m
[32m+[m[32muvicorn app.main:app --reload[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Terminal 2 — Start the frontend[m
[32m+[m[32mcd frontend[m
[32m+[m[32mnpm run dev[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe app will be available at `http://localhost:5173` (or as shown in your terminal).[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32mBackend API docs are available at `http://localhost:8000/docs`.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 🔄 Workflow[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Upload documents via the UI[m
[32m+[m[32m2. System extracts, chunks, and embeds the text[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Embeddings are stored in the vector database[m
